{"sequence":48,"timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:43:57.119414451Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-57793a7e","body":"`bin/rb-lite` does not fingerprint symlink worktree content correctly. At line 113 it skips any path where `[[ -f $path ]]` is false, so dangling symlinks and symlinks to directories have no worktree content in the fingerprint; at line 115 it hashes symlink targets via `sha256sum` rather than the symlink text Git stores. If an implementer retargets an already-dirty symlink, `git status` and the index can remain unchanged while the actual git diff changes, causing the loop to declare stability too early. Hash symlink contents explicitly, for example by detecting `[[ -L $path ]]` and hashing `readlink \"$path\"` with an unambiguous prefix instead of following or skipping the link.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"7d5cdfc2d2846843bd42607073cc27227d6c2387124f5053c03ee29aca071e89","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260501071400","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
